List of integer sequences with links to LODA programs.

* [A050140](https://oeis.org/A050140) ([program](/edit/?oeis=50140)): a(n) = 2*floor(n*phi)-n, where phi = (1+sqrt(5))/2.

* [A060587](https://oeis.org/A060587) ([program](/edit/?oeis=60587)): A ternary code: inverse of A060583.

* [A060593](https://oeis.org/A060593) ([program](/edit/?oeis=60593)): a(n) is the number of ways that a cycle of length 2n+1 in the symmetric group S_(2n+1) can be decomposed as the product of two cycles of length 2n+1.
* [A060602](https://oeis.org/A060602) ([program](/edit/?oeis=60602)): Number of d-dimensional tilings of unary zonotopes. The zonotope Z(D,d) is the projection of the D-dimensional hypercube onto the d-dimensional space and the tiles are the projections of the d-dimensional faces of the hypercube. Here the codimension, i.e., D-d, is constant = 3 and d varies from 0 to ...

* [A060604](https://oeis.org/A060604) ([program](/edit/?oeis=60604)): a(n) = binomial(prime(n), n) where prime(n) = n-th prime.
* [A060605](https://oeis.org/A060605) ([program](/edit/?oeis=60605)): a(n) = sum of lengths of the iteration sequences of Euler totient function from 1 to n.
* [A060606](https://oeis.org/A060606) ([program](/edit/?oeis=60606)): The n-th term is the sum of lengths of iteration chains to get fixed points(=1) for the Euler totient function from 1 to n.
* [A060607](https://oeis.org/A060607) ([program](/edit/?oeis=60607)): Number of iterations of phi(x) at prime(n) needed to reach 1.
* [A060610](https://oeis.org/A060610) ([program](/edit/?oeis=60610)): Repeatedly apply Euler phi to the n-th prime; a(n) is the number of terms in the resulting iteration chain which are not powers of 2 (number of initial iterations until reaching the first power of 2).
* [A060615](https://oeis.org/A060615) ([program](/edit/?oeis=60615)): Number of conjugacy classes in the group GL_2(K) when K is a finite field with q = p^m for a prime p and m >= 1.

* [A060621](https://oeis.org/A060621) ([program](/edit/?oeis=60621)): Number of flips between the d-dimensional tilings of the unary zonotope Z(D,d). Here the codimension D-d is equal to 3 and d varies.

* [A060633](https://oeis.org/A060633) ([program](/edit/?oeis=60633)): Surround numbers of an n X 1 rectangle.
